    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 67 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "If the RMS current is 2A, the average power delivered to a circuit is ___",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "240W",
        "1100W",
        "60W",
        "170W"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "240W"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "RMS voltage \\( V_{\\text{rms}} = \\frac{120}{\\sqrt{2}} \\approx 84.85 \\, \\text{V} \\). Power \\( P = V_{\\text{rms}} I_{\\text{rms}} = (84.85)(2) \\approx 170 \\, \\text{W} \\). (Note: Closest option is 240W, but exact calculation suggests 170W. Verify generator context.)"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism",
      "Alternating Current",
      "Circuit Analysis",
